STRATEGY DESIGN PATTERN:
ENCAPSULATIING A FAMILY OF ALGORITHMS OR BEHAVIOURS INTO SEPERATE CLASSES AND MAKING THEM INTERCHANGABLE.
"Strategy means:Take the part of your program that might change in the future and separate it from the part that stays the same".

Example:
Imagine you're ordering food.
You tell the delivery app:
"Get me my food."
The app has multiple delivery partners:
Swiggy Genie
Dunzo
Porter
The app doesn't care which one actually delivers the food. It only knows:
"I need someone to deliver this order."
At the last moment, it chooses one of the delivery partners.
That's Strategy.

Without Strategy:
If Swiggy available
    use Swiggy
Else if Dunzo available
    use Dunzo
Else if Porter available
    use Porter 

With Strategy:
Swiggy Delivery
Dunzo Delivery
Porter Delivery    

Components:
--Strategy Interface (Define common behaviour)
--Concrete Strategies (Implement different algorithms)
--Context class(Uses a strategy)
--Client code(Chooses the strategy)